{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_55","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator:2.15.0-alpha`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5848-fails-javac-compile-io.opentelemetry.instrumentation-opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator-2.15.0-alpha-656dc16f\n\nThe first failing stage was `:compileTestJava`. In `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator:2.15.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T22-30-44-295945Z.log`, the generated `2.15.0-alpha` test still uses the old DB semconv API from `2.1.0-alpha`: `DatabaseGetter` implements `DbClientAttributesGetter<DatabaseRequest>`, but `2.15.0-alpha` expects the newer `DbClientAttributesGetter<REQUEST, RESPONSE>` shape, and the extractor/span-name factory calls fail because the DB getter method names/signatures changed (`getSystem`/`getName`/`getStatement`/`getOperation` vs `getDbSystem`/`getDbNamespace`/`getDbQueryText`/`getDbOperationName`).\n\nThere is evidence the automation found a transient fix but did not preserve it. `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator:2.15.0-alpha/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T22-32-02-010524Z.log` shows edits to switch `DatabaseGetter` to `DbClientAttributesGetter<DatabaseRequest, Void>` and rename those DB getter overrides, and the follow-up Gradle retries in `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator:2.15.0-alpha/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-04T22-32-02-018337Z.log`, `.../gradle-test-2026-05-04T22-33-11-446617Z.log`, and `.../gradle-test-2026-05-04T22-33-55-297582Z.log` are `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`. However, `stats/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation/opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator/2.15.0-alpha/execution-metrics.json` still records `status: failure`, `generated_loc: 0`, `ending_commit` unchanged at `66ba7f530cfb2c9c9fd08d6cd475392a0e4468a8`, and `test_file` / `metadata_file` as `None`, so the successful local fix was not durably recorded in the preserved branch.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Recreate the `2.15.0-alpha` test changes from `human-intervention-logs/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator:2.15.0-alpha/fix-javac-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-04T22-32-02-010524Z.log`, especially the DB getter generic and renamed method updates.\n2. Re-run `./gradlew compileTestJava -Pcoordinates=io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator:2.15.0-alpha` and then `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.opentelemetry.instrumentation:opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator:2.15.0-alpha`.\n3. If that passes, restore and commit the `tests/src/io.opentelemetry.instrumentation/opentelemetry-instrumentation-api-incubator/2.15.0-alpha` files on top of the preserved branch."}}
